name: Oddish
flavorText: Its scientific name is "Oddium Wanderus." At night, it is said to walk nearly 1,000 feet on its two roots.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Gloom
flavorText: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.

name: Vileplume
flavorText: It has the world's largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.
Ability1Text: Each player can't play any Item cards from his or her hand.

name: Bellossom
flavorText: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Move as many Grass Energy attached to your Pokemon to your other Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Spinarak
flavorText: It lies still in the same pose for days in its web, waiting for its unsuspecting prey to wander close.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Ariados
flavorText: It attaches silk to its prey and sets it free. Later, it tracks the silk to the prey and its friends.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this Ability. Both Active Pokemon (except for Grass Pokemon) are now Poisoned.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Sceptile-EX
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep and Poisoned.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: M Sceptile-EX
Attack1Text: You may attach up to 2 Grass Energy cards from your hand to your Benched Pokemon in any way you like. If you attached Energy to a Pokemon in this way, heal all damage from that Pokemon.

name: Combee
flavorText: It collects and delivers honey to its colony. At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep.

name: Vespiquen
flavorText: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by Combee.
Attack1Text: You may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Pokemon in your discard pile.

name: Vespiquen
flavorText: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by Combee.
Attack1Text: Heal from this Pokemon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

name: Virizion
flavorText: Legends say this Pokemon confounded opponents with its swift movements.
Attack1Text: Put 2 Pokemon from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack2Text: If you have more Prize cards left than your opponent, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Flareon
flavorText: It has a flame bag inside its body. After inhaling deeply, it blows out flames of nearly 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.
Ability1Text: Each of your Stage 1 Pokemon in play is now a Fire Pokemon in addition to its existing types.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Entei
flavorText: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.
Attack1Text: Discard the top 4 cards of your deck. If any of those cards are Fire Energy cards, attach them to your Pokemon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.

name: Entei
flavorText: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokemon by attacks is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokemon does 30 damage to itself.

name: Larvesta
flavorText: The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes. They shoot fire from their five horns to repel attacking enemies.

name: Volcarona
flavorText: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona's fire provided a replacement for the sun.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokemon and put it onto your Bench. Then, search your deck for up to 2 basic Energy cards and attach them to that Pokemon. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Volcarona
flavorText: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona's fire provided a replacement for the sun.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.
Attack2Text: Your opponent switches his or her Active Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.

name: Magikarp
flavorText: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Gyarados
flavorText: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage to each Benched Pokemon (both yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: Flip a coin for each Water Energy attached to this Pokemon. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

name: Gyarados
flavorText: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each damage counter on each of your Benched Magikarp.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage. If tails, this Pokemon does 30 damage to itself.

name: Vaporeon
flavorText: It has evolved to be suitable for an aquatic life. It can invisibly melt away into water.
Ability1Text: Each of your Stage 1 Pokemon in play is now a Water Pokemon in addition to its existing types.

name: Relicanth
flavorText: A rare Pokemon discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Pokemon Tool cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Regice
flavorText: Its body is made of ice from the ice age. It controls frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokemon by Pokemon-EX.

name: Kyurem-EX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokemon. The Defending Pokemon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Jolteon
flavorText: It accumulates negative ions in the atmosphere to blast out 10,000-volt lightning bolts.
Ability1Text: Each of your Stage 1 Pokemon in play is now a Lightning Pokemon in addition to its existing types.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Ampharos-EX
Attack1Text: Look at the top 4 cards of your deck and attach as many Lightning Energy cards you find there as you like to this Pokemon. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, or any other effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: M Ampharos-EX
Attack1Text: You may do 50 more damage and leave your opponent's Active Pokemon Paralyzed. If you do, this Pokemon does 30 damage to itself.

name: Rotom
flavorText: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. For each heads, choose a random card from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals that card and shuffles it into his or her deck.

name: Unown
flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokemon is on your Bench, you may discard this Pokemon and all cards attached to it (this does not count as a Knock Out). If you do, draw a card.

name: Baltoy
flavorText: It moves by spinning on its foot. It is a rare Pokemon that was discovered in ancient ruins.

name: Baltoy
flavorText: It moves by spinning on its foot. It is a rare Pokemon that was discovered in ancient ruins.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 3 cards of either player's deck and put them back on top of that player's deck in any order.

name: Claydol
flavorText: It is said that it originates from clay dolls made by an ancient civilization.
Attack1Text: Devolve each of your opponent's evolved Pokemon and put the highest Stage Evolution card on it into your opponent's hand.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Golett
flavorText: Ancient science fashioned this Pokemon from clay. It's been active for thousands of years.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Golurk
flavorText: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is in play, it is Psychic and Fighting type.
Attack1Text: You may do 40 more damage. If you do, this Pokemon does 20 damage to itself.

name: Hoopa-EX
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench, you may search your deck for up to 3 Pokemon-EX (except for Hoopa-EX), reveal them, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Machamp-EX
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage times the number of damage counters on this Pokemon. This Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 80 more damage. Then, remove all Special Conditions from this Pokemon.

name: Wooper
flavorText: When the temperature cools in the evening, they emerge from water to seek food along the shore.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Quagsire
flavorText: This carefree Pokemon has an easy-going nature. While swimming, it always bumps into boat hulls.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Regirock
flavorText: The same rocks that form its body have been found in ground layers around the world.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon-EX, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Golurk
flavorText: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.

name: Tyranitar-EX

name: M Tyranitar-EX
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Sableye

Attack1Text: Choose a Supporter card from your opponent's discard pile and use it as the effect of this attack.
Attack2Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Inkay
flavorText: It flashes the light-emitting spots on its body, which drains its opponent's will to fight. It takes the opportunity to scuttle away and hide.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

flavorText: It lures prey close with hypnotic motions, then wraps its tentacles around it before finishing it off with digestive fluids.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with his or her Active Pokemon. The new Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: Put a card from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Beldum
flavorText: It converses with others by magnetic pulses. In a swarm, they move in perfect unison.

name: Metang
flavorText: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its two brains are linked, amplifying its psychic power.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

name: Metagross
flavorText: Metang combined to form it. With four brains, it has the intelligence of a supercomputer.

name: Metagross

name: Registeel
flavorText: Its body is said to be harder than any kind of metal. A study has revealed that its body is hollow.

Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon-EX, discard an Energy attached to that Pokemon.

name: Ralts
flavorText: It is highly attuned to the emotions of people and Pokemon. It hides if it senses hostility.

name: Kirlia
flavorText: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Gardevoir
flavorText: It has the power to predict the future. Its power peaks when it is protecting its Trainer.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may heal 20 damage from each of your Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Cottonee
flavorText: Perhaps because they feel more at ease in a group, they stick to others they find. They end up looking like a cloud.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Whimsicott
flavorText: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

name: Giratina-EX

name: Sliggoo
flavorText: Its four horns are a high-performance radar system. It uses them to sense sounds and smells, rather than using ears or a nose.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Goodra

name: Meowth
flavorText: Adores round objects. It wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon has any Darkness Energy attached to it, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Persian

Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokemon conceals many different possible evolutions.

name: Porygon
